parameters:
--Stamina and skill power have been \c[24]fully
restored\c[0]!

My name is Nezumi Komachi! Kiridou Gamen, just as the notice
predicted, I've come to beat you down!

Kukukuku. You didn't die from a pitfall? Fitting for someone
who calls themselves a mouse. You're a nimble one.

I saw a woman made to look like a fake in front of your
mansion. What's the meaning of preparing a decoy of me?

Of course, it was to lure you out. I thought if there's
someone compassionate enough to distribute stolen money to
the people of Edo, they would come to save the decoy--

You've brazenly come to my mansion all alone. If you won't
die from a pitfall, then I have no choice but to slice you
up with my swordsmanship.

(Ah, that was close...! I could have been split in two if I
had misstepped!)

Hmph. To dodge my first strike, your movements are indeed
commendable. It's no wonder you've managed to pull off so
many thefts without getting caught by the magistrate's
office.

This is a masterwork katana forged by a famous Bizen
swordsmith. I'll grant you the honor of being cut down by a
famous sword. Come at me, Nezumi Komachi--!
Lord Gamen! I shall assist you!
--Kiridou Gamen and his skilled musketeers are attacking!
This won't be enough to stop my attack! Take this--!
--Guaahh!? Idiot...! My famous sword, it broke!?
Eek!? The bullets were dodged!? How fast--!?

My anger hasn't subsided yet... I absolutely can't forgive
you for preparing an unrelated fake to lure me out. I'll
make you suffer even more! Here--!

I'll forgive you in exchange for the chest of a thousand
ry. I can't go back empty-handed after breaking into steal,
now can I?
Lord Gamen! Damn you, Nezumi Komachi--!
Release our lord! We have more numbers on our side!

Don't move! If you come any closer, I'll shove this
chopstick up your precious lord's nose, got it?

Guh! The lord has been taken hostage...!? H-how cowardly,
Nezumi Komachi!

What's cowardly? You're the one who involved an innocent
woman just to lure me out... The real cowardice and
wickedness is on your side! Take this!
Gahh...!? Stop it! I beg for mercy...!

So what will it be, Kiridou Gamen? Will you meet my demand
for the chest of a thousand ry as a fee? Or will you not?

Ugh! You lot, prepare the chest of a thousand ry! Hurry
up--! Make haste!

Hmmph! You're quite efficient, which is good. I really want
more, but carrying too much is heavy, so I'll just take this
much

Wait! Nezumi Komachi! Your rampage ends here! Release Lord
Kiridou!

A woman who was imprisoned in the Kiridou family's mansion
came to the magistrate's office. But who would have thought
the real Nezumi Komachi was here...!

(Thank goodness. The woman who was made into a decoy has
been properly protected.)
Nezumi Komachi! You won't escape! You're under arrest--!

Haha! It's too late to come now I'll be taking the chest of
a thousand ry this time as well! Farewell--!
Nuuu!? A smoke screen...!? I can't see anything!
Ahaha! Goodbye, officers of the magistrate's office!
--Karin has escaped from the Kiridou family's mansion!

Don't let her get away! Chase after Nezumi Komachi,
everyone!

...! (What a situation. To think that a theft could be
pulled off so brazenly in a daimyo's mansion so close to Edo
Castle...!)
Gold coins are falling from the sky!?

Come on, come on, it's Nezumi Komachi's haul for today!
Those who want it, pick it up! It's the usual lavish
giveaway!

--Karin scattered the stolen gold coins throughout Edo until
dawn!
...Phew. I got too excited last night...
Extra, extra! Another feat by Nezumi Komachi!

Ohh! Nezumi Komachi, huh? Which house did she break into
this time?

This time, believe it or not! She broke into the grand
daimyo Kiridou family in Hibiya! She mowed down the samurai
guards and the head of the family, Lord Gamen, stole the
chest of a thousand ry and distributed the gold coins to
the townspeople!

She broke into a samurai's residence instead of a wealthy
merchant's? That's amazing!

... (Hehe, it's good that Nezumi Komachi's name is getting
even more famous)
Uguh... Karin, big sister... Uh, uhh...!
Are you okay, Omitsu-chan? Tell me clearly what happened?
It's... Grandfather says... he has to commit seppuku...
Eh!? Seppuku--!? Why would he have to do that!?

Because he let Nezumi Komachi escape... As the head of the
magistrate's office tasked with protecting Edo, Grandfather
says he must take responsibility...
Wah-ehn, wah-ehn! Nooo--!! Don't leave me behind! Daddy!

...Don't cry, Karin. It makes father sad to see you cry like
that. No more tears now...

But... because Daddy said he might not come back...!
*sniffle*, *sniffle*...!

...It's just a possibility. If I don't return, you must rely
on Oei-dono, understand?

*sob*... *sniffle*...! What will I do if Grandfather
dies...!

...It's okay, Omitsu-chan. I won't let you be separated from
your grandfather... No more crying...

He's going to commit seppuku because Nezumi Komachi wasn't
caught, right? Then... I'll go catch her...
--!? Eh... catch Nezumi Komachi...? You, Karin-oneechan!?

Yes. I'll catch her quickly. So no more tears, okay? Right,
Omitsu-chan...

...Well then. Take care, Omitsu-chan. And please give my
regards to Oei-san.

--Karin gently stroked Omitsu's head before leaving the
place with a sad look in her eyes.
Tamba-sama! Are you serious?! To take your own life...!?

Ah. Despite receiving numerous warning letters, we failed to
capture her, and now with a daimyo's residence right in
front of Edo Castle being attacked by Nezumi Komachi, the
Edo Magistrate's honor is at stake. It's a blunder worthy of
seppuku.

Kyuma. This is the way of the samurai. I'm sorry to ask, but
I need you to be my second.
What has happened! This situation is grave!

That's just it...! A girl claiming to be Nezumi Komachi has
appeared in front of the magistrate's office!
...Yes. I am the phantom thief Nezumi Komachi--no lies.

--Karin turned herself in at the magistrate's office of her
own volition.
